// Adversarial: Corridor layout funnels the breaker into repeated wall contacts
// by narrowing lateral movement range. High action_prob (0.9) drives near-maximum
// dash frequency, so the breaker hits the left and right walls many times per
// second. This exercises the BreakerImpactWall dispatch path, which is distinct
// from BoltImpactWall — it fires when the breaker body reaches the lateral
// playfield boundary and is clamped by BreakerPositionClamped.
// Risks: if BreakerImpactWall fires an effect that modifies bolt velocity, and
// the bolt is simultaneously near a wall, two impulses can compound in the same
// fixed-update tick. BoltSpeedInRange catches velocity going outside [min, max].
// BreakerInBounds guards against the clamp system failing to prevent the breaker
// from escaping bounds on a rapid successive-dash sequence. NoNaN guards against
// floating-point corruption from repeated wall-snap corrections at high velocity.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Corridor",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.9)),
    max_frames: 6000,
    invariants: [NoNaN, BoltInBounds, BreakerInBounds, BoltSpeedInRange],
    expected_violations: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 2207,
)
